Invalid bundle for an in-toto DSSE envelope logged to Rekor v2 with the
new hashedrekord-over-DSSE encoding (kind=hashedrekord/0.0.2). The
envelope signature does not verify under the bundle's certificate (it was
made with a different key entirely). The TSA timestamp matches the
envelope signature, so it should not produce a timestamp failure.

Construction:
  1. Sign in-toto statement A as DSSE with key/cert #1 → bundle1
     (happy-path source)
  2. Sign in-toto statement A as DSSE with an unrelated key/cert #2 →
     bundle2
  3. In bundle1, replace the envelope signature and the RFC3161 timestamps
     with those from bundle2.

Signed against staging Sigstore using the
sigstore-conformance/extremely-dangerous-public-oidc-beacon workflow
identity. The bundle ships its own trusted_root.json (the staging trust
root); once production has a Rekor v2 instance the custom trust root can
be removed.
